--- OVERVIEW: Train_PPiMg2_LFER/scripts ---

Analysis scripts synced from MareNostrum 5 (supervisor's account uv169161, reserved area) on
05/07/2026.

o FES_2D.py: builds a 2D free-energy surface from biased/reweighted collective-variable
  trajectories (produces the FES_2D.png plots under ../LFER_3_mg2/pph4/).

o FES_2D_inverse.py: variant of FES_2D.py using the inverse mapping of the reaction
  coordinates, used as a cross-check of the surface reconstruction.

o FES_from_Reweighting.py: reconstructs the free-energy surface via trajectory reweighting
  (rather than direct histogramming), for OPES/metadynamics-biased runs.

o convert_restart_to_lmp.py: converts a LAMMPS restart file from an SMD run into a plain
  LAMMPS data/topology (.lmp) file, used to seed each umbrella-sampling window.

o average_PMF.py: averages the per-replica WHAM free-energy profiles into the combined
  average_pmf.png reported for each umbrella-sampling scan.

o generate_US_window.py: builds a single umbrella-sampling window input (restraint center,
  force constant, starting configuration) for a PLUMED/LAMMPS umbrella-sampling scan.

Note: wham1D.py / errors_wham1D.py (WHAM reconstruction and its error estimate) are identical
to the copies already documented in ../../Training_2Mgcomplex/scripts/README and were not
duplicated here.

Note: written 05/07/2026 to describe newly-synced scripts; no existing file was modified.
